; FILED: a self tail call through a `when` body is not tail-call-optimized:
; FRAME OVERFLOW at depth ~300 (stderr diagnostic, exit code 0, no output).
; The identical loop written with `if` runs fine (TCO applied).
; native -r : ok
; vm        : <no stdout>, "FRAME OVERFLOW" on stderr, exit code 0
(let lp ((i 0)) (when (< i 300) (lp (+ i 1))))
(display "ok")
